[SN]TITLE[SN]
Falls Road, Belfast: Teenager charged after car theft from convent

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 15-year-old teenager has been charged with burglary and four driving offences in connection with the theft of a car in west Belfast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The vehicle was taken from a convent in the Falls Road area on Thursday night.
The youth is charged with dangerous driving, aggravated vehicle taking causing damage to the car, using a motor vehicle without insurance and driving whilst disqualified by reason of age.
He is due to appear in court on Monday.
